0=No history of significant mood elevation, recurrent depression, or psychosis; 2=Any recurrent typical unipolar major depressive disorder, history of any kind of psychotic disorder; 5=Clear cut hypomania secondary to antidepressant use, episodes with characteristic sxs of hypomania/but sxs/duration/intensity are subthreshold for hypomania or cyclothymia, a single MDE with psychotic or atypical features, any postpartum depression; 10=Clear cut hypomania with no significant general medical or known secondary etiology, clear cut cyclothymia with no significant general medical or known secondary etiology, clear cut mania secondary to antidepressant use; 15=Clear cut acute mixed episode or dysphoric or irritable mania with no significant general medical or known secondary etiology; 20=Documented acute mania or mixed episode with prominent euphoria, grandiosity, or expansiveness and no significant general medical or known secondary etiology
0=No history of affective illness; 5=after age 45; 10=30-45 years; 15=before age 15 or between 20 and 30; 20=15-19 years

0=None of the above; 2=Baseline hyperthymic personality, marriage 3 or more times, in two or more years has started a new job and changed jobs after less than a year, has more than two advanced degrees; 5=Recurrent unipolar MDD with 3 or more MDE, recurrent and distinct hypomanic episodes without full inter episode recovery, recurrent medication non compliance, comorbid borderline personality disorder/anxiety disorders/eating disorders/history of ADHD, engagement in risky behaviors that pose a problem for patient/family/friends, behavioral evidence of perimenstrual exacerbation of mood symptoms; 10=Comorbid substance abuse, psychotic features only during acute mood episodes, incarceration or repeated legal offences related to manic behavior; 15=Recurrent and distinct manic episodes with incomplete inter episode recovery, recurrent and distinct hypomanic episodes with full inter episode recovery; 20=Recurrent and distinct manic episodes separated by periods of full recovery

0=None of the above or no treatment; 2=Immediate near complete response to antidepressant withdrawal; 5=Treatment resistance-lack of response to complete trials of 3 or more antidepressants, affective switch to mania or hypomania with antidepressant withdrawal; 10=Worsening dysphoria or mixed symptoms during antidepressant treatment subthreshold for mania, partial response to one or two mood stabilizers within 12 weeks of therapeutic treatment, antidepressant induced new or worsening rapid cycling course; 15=Full recovery within 12 weeks of therapeutic treatment with mood stabilizing medication or relapse withing 12 weeks of discontinuing tx, affective switch to mania within 12 weeks of starting a new antidepressant or increasing dose; 20=Full recovery within 4 weeks of therapeutic treatment with mood stabilizing medication

0=None of the above or no family psychiatric illnesses; 2=First degree relative with possible recurrent unipolar MDD, first degree relative with diagnosed related illness; 5=First degree relative with documented substance abuse, and relative with possible bipolar illness; 10=First degree relative with documented recurrent unipolar MDD or schizoaffective disorder, any relative with documented bipolar illness or recurrent unipolar MDD and behavioral evidence suggesting bipolar illness; 15=At least one second degree relative with documented bipolar illness, at least one first degree relative with documented recurrent unipolar MDD and behavioral evidence suggesting bipolar illness; 20=At least one first degree relative with documented bipolar illness
